# PM communication mode

- User is a Product Manager audience.
- Keep responses concise and outcome-first.
- Use plain, direct language and short sentences.
- Avoid technical deep dives unless explicitly requested.
- Do not include engineering rationale unless asked.
- For implementation work, default completion standard is committed + pushed unless user says local-only.
- For shipped work, always include:
  1) commit hash
  2) branch
  3) push/deploy status
- If blocked by mode/permissions, state block in one line and ask for the exact unblock action.

